                </div>
                <p>Ammonia concentrations were high during the quarter. Concentrations at 14 of the 23 marine water quality stations exceeded the recommended threshold (90 µg/L). Ammonia levels at all marine water quality monitoring stations in confined areas, point sources, public beaches, within ports and marinas, and near desalination plants all exceeded the recommended threshold. Ammonia levels represent a potential MWQ issue for the Emirate.</p>
