                <div class="section-title">
                    <small><i class="icon-time append"></i></a>Last updated on 1st of April, 18:23 by Dr. Anybody | <a href="">View indicator</a></small>
                    <h2>Enterococci</h2>
                    <h3>Enterococci levels (MON/100 ml) in Abu Dabhi Emirate waters.</h3>
                </div>
                <p>Enterococci concentrations were elevated within Abu Dhabi's marine environment. Enterococci are monitored at all stations and concentrations at two of those stations exceeded the recommended threshold (280 MPN/100ml) during the first quarter of 2013. Enterococci concentrations were elevated in confined areas and point sources, but not at public beaches. Enterococci concentrations are an indicator of sewage contamination and thus an important parameter to monitor within the Emirate's marine environment.</p>
                <img src="/images/visualisations/06.png" alt="visualisation 6">
            </section>
