                <ul>
                    <li>Multispecies micro algal bloom near Emirates Steel Plant (occurred Jan. 14, 2013).</li>
                    <li>Algal bloom near ADNEC (Feb. 19, 2013) Phytoplankton qualitative analysis confirmed the bloom was due to Oscillatoria sp (Cyanobacteria) and Pseudo-nitzschia sp.</li>
                    <li>Weekly water quality monitoring of storm drain outfalls and ambient marine water along Eastern Corniche due to odor complaints was initiated in February and continues to date. High levels of nutrients and enterococci detected.</li>
                    <li>Occurrence of Cochlodinium polykrikoides (Feb 2013). During routine algal bloom monitoring the MWQ team recorded harmful dinoflagellate Cochlodinium polykrikoides for the first time in Abu Dabhi Emimrate waters. Fortunately the cell concentrations was low, and the species disappeared after a week.</li>
