                    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
                </div>
                <p>The marine environment is an important economic and cultural component of Abu Dabhi. Thus, monitoring marine water quality is vital to the continuation and sustainability of the Emirate's fisheries, other marine biota and human health issues can all arise from elevated concentrations, of certain pollutants and water quality parameters. Therefore, the monitoring of marine water quality is an important longterm strategy for maintaning the health of Abu Dabhi's Marine Enviroment.</p>
